<!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><br>
<br>
Friends,<br>
<br>
I speak with the voice of The Virtuous Man, who is calling all of cunning and ingenuity to join with him in the forming of a gathering, the likes of which Norrath has yet to behold. If you are light of fingers, strong of arm, quiet in movement, adept at...story-telling, experienced in...em... locksmithing, and...uh...believe that every person has a good side, which is usually the back side, The Virtuous Man seeks you.<br>
<br>
Be assured that The Virtuous Man discriminates naught against race or religion, and is a firm believer of meritocracy. The Virtuous Man has great plans for Norrath, among which include: enrichment of the needy, cleaning and disposal services, courier services specifically tailored to the movement of high-value items, lost-and-found shops for items that the general populace always seem to lose, home and person protection services, and the list goes on.<br>
<br>
If your values are in agreement with those of The Virtuous Man, please contact me, Kraye, humble servant of The Virtuous Man.<br>
<br>
Very Truly Yours,<br>
<br>
Kraye<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><br>
<br>
OOC Description:<br>
<br>
A new thieves' guild is looking to get organized on the Firiona Vie server. We are looking to base the guild on &quot;The Mockers&quot; as described in Raymond E. Fiest's Riftwar series of novels. The guild will be open to Bards, Rangers, Rogues and Warriors and has no restriction regarding Race or Religion. Being a Firiona Vie guild, the guild will be oriented towards role-playing. Forseen activities for the guild include: pick-pocketing &quot;raids&quot; on cities and other areas, assassination services for various other FV guilds, smuggling of city-specific goods (for races that are KoS to a certain city), possibly a loan services or a pawn shop, and other similar not-so-legal type activies.<br>
<br>
If you are interested and have, or woud like to play, a Bard, Ranger, Rogue or Warrior on the Firiona Vie server, please contact me (Kraye) in game, or send me an email at kraye_fv@yahoo.co.jp<br>
<br>
Cheers,<br>
Kraye <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kraye>Kraye</A> at: 3/31/03 1:06:12 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gaspfv>Gasp FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>AKA Brevis</span><br>  Posts: 48<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/10/03 9:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=480.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Guild of Rogues</span><hr size=1> While this is an interesting idea, I think the guild will be a very hard sell.<br>
